 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search MD/ DO/ PA/ NP - Phoenix AZ The Wound Pros, LLC Phoenix, AZ Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description The Wound Pros is a nationwide Wound Care Medical Group. Our full-service wound care strategy has added enormous value to patients who are homebound or reside in long-term facilities across the country by providing an array of essential tools including: Digital Wound Management, Telemedicine, Advanced EHR System, Mobile Vascular Assessment, Digital Supply tracking, as well as Advanced Wound Care Dressings.
 By leveraging the power of Artificial Intelligence, we have been able to heal wounds faster and more efficiently. By joining our team, you will be able to be a part of our mission to heal wounds and prevent amputations in long-term care facilities.
 We are seeking MD/ DO/ NP/ PAs in various markets across the country to provide and manage advanced wound care to patients who are homebound patients or in long-term care facilities.
 Don't have Wound Care Experience? No worries, we will train you and help you get certified. 
 Responsibilities and Duties: 
 Perform complete physical exams of patients. Select, order, and perform tests and procedures to best treat the patient. Perform wound care procedures as deemed necessary and appropriate for plan of care in accordance to Wound Pros 6 Step Treatment Protocol. Define and document patient diagnoses. Recommendations for prescription of required medications and/or Surgical/Wound Care Dressings to facilitate wound healing and/or wound prevention. Assure all patients are completely satisfied, by exemplifying Wound Pros standards for patient care. Patient education and management Assists with special projects as needed. Debridement of wounds by various methods completed safely during the patient visit. Application of topical wound care and other wound management products Notate findings and treatment course in patient chart, including follow-up notes. Actively participate in departmental activities to improve training methods and achieve company goals. Travel to patients' homes and/or long re facilities is be required.
 Qualifications: 
 MD/DOs must be a graduate of an accredited school of Allopathic Medicine or Osteopathic Medicine. Physician's Assistants should be a graduate of an accredited Certified Physicians Assistants Program  License to practice Medicine as a MD/ DO/ NP or PA-C with a current valid state license.  Patient-centric approach Excellent verbal and written communication skills in a professional environment Must be proficient with medical instruments and equipment required by Wound Pros. Ability to communicate effectively, in verbal and written form. Sound understanding of all federal and state regulations. Ability to lift 50 lbs. or more. Must have full range of mobility. Must be able to reposition patients. Valid and unrestricted driver's license
 Why work for The Wound Pros? 
 Highly competitive compensation package You conduct the initial evaluation, and all follow up visits. You will have the full support of Wound Care Certified Nurses for consultation Comprehensive benefits package ( 100% Employee covered Medical Plan ) Health Dental Vision  Mileage Reimbursement The Wound Pros, LLC 30+ days ago original job If you require alternative methods of application or screening, you must approach the employer directly to request this as Indeed is not responsible for the employer's application process. Report job Apply Now Apply Now Save this job Save this job Nurse Practitioner jobs in Phoenix, AZ Jobs at The Wound Pros in Phoenix, AZ Nurse Practitioner salaries in Phoenix, AZ Company Info Follow Get job updates from The Wound Pros, LLC Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume Hiring Lab Career Advice Browse Jobs Browse Companies Salaries Find Certifications Indeed Events Work at Indeed Countries About Help Center Â© 2021 Indeed Do Not Sell My Personal Information Accessibility at Indeed Privacy Center Cookies Privacy Terms Let Employers Find You Upload Your Resume 
 
 
 
 
 
